  "prompt": "How much percentage of inorganic organic and water present in enamel cementum and dentine?",
  "response": "The composition of dental tissues\u2014enamel, cementum, and dentin\u2014varies in terms of inorganic, organic, and water content. Here's a breakdown:\n\n### 1. **Enamel**\n   - **Inorganic content**: ~96%\n     - Primarily hydroxyapatite (calcium phosphate crystals).\n   - **Organic content**: ~1%\n     - Proteins like amelogenins and enamelins.\n   - **Water content**: ~3%\n     - Bound within the enamel structure.\n\n### 2. **Cementum**\n   - **Inorganic content**: ~45-50%\n     - Hydroxyapatite crystals.\n   - **Organic content**: ~50-55%\n     - Collagen fibers and other proteins.\n   - **Water content**: ~2-3%\n     - Similar to enamel but slightly less.\n\n### 3. **Dentin**\n   - **Inorganic content**: ~70%\n     - Hydroxyapatite crystals.\n   - **Organic content**: ~20%\n     - Collagen fibers and other proteins.\n   - **Water content**: ~10%\n     - Bound within the dentin structure.\n\n### Summary Table:\n| Tissue   | Inorganic Content | Organic Content | Water Content |\n|----------|-------------------|-----------------|---------------|\n| Enamel   | ~96%             | ~1%             | ~3%           |\n| Cementum | ~45-50%          | ~50-55%         | ~2-3%         |\n| Dentin   | ~70%             | ~20%            | ~10%          |\n\nThese percentages are approximate and can vary slightly depending on factors like age, location in the tooth, and individual variability.",
